For KSP 1.3.1:

The KSP.log is in your KSP install directory, the same directory which contains the KSP.exe. The output_log is in: 'KSP_Install_directory\KSP_Data\'

You might want to choose a file hosting service that doesn't require outside users to actually download a file, which I, in particular, are very wary of.   DropBox and googledrive allow this sort of access.   This looks like a pretty good cloud service, but for a single user or a group of trusted users.

Ok, let's see..

Your paging file runs out of memory but there is still some physical memory left so this should not be the problem. For testing purposes, you might want to increase it anyway.

For some reason, the output_log and ksp.log don't show a crash but some issues regarding firespitter. The version installed is pretty old, there is an updated one for KSP 1.3. : https://github.com/snjo/Firespitter/releases/tag/v7.6.0

not all of my mods are for 1.3.1 but what i dont understand is why it has always worked up to this point, just one day it crashed and its been this way for like 2 weeks idk its very strange

Well, it is strange indeed but the firespitter mod is not the only one with a wrong version, for example: ClickThoughBlocker 0.1.6.9 is build for KSP 1.5.1.

While most mods seem to be installed in the correct version, you should check this for each mod. That's a tedious work but unfortunately necessary.
